          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The secondary beam containing Be-11 ions with a",
                "kinetic energy of 520 MeV/nucleon was produced in",
                "fragmentation reactions of a primary Ar-40 beam",
                "delivered by the heavy-ion synchrotron SIS at GSI. The",
                " 720 MeV/nucleon Ar-40 beam with an intensity of about",
                " 10E+10 ion per second impinged on a beryllium",
                " production target of 5 g/cm**2 thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The secondary targets, natural carbon target and",
                "natural lead target, 0.573 g/cm**2 and 1.820 g/cm**2",
                "thicknesses, respectively were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCH"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "FRS"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Fragments were selected according to",
                " magnetic rigidity by the fragment separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Be-10 fragments, neutrons and gamma rays have",
                " been detected in coincidence."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two thin plastic scintillation detectors were",
                "used for determination the mass-to-charge ratio",
                "obtained from a time-of-flight measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The position of the incoming particles on the",
                "target was measured by a position-sensitive Si pin-",
                "diode."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma rays emitted from excited Be-10",
                " fragments were detected by the 4-pi Crystal Ball",
                " spectrometer, consisting of 160 NaI detectors. Behind",
                " the target, the fragments were deflected by a large-",
                " gap dippole magnet ALADIN.",
                "The neutron were detected in the LAND neutron detector",
                "having an active area of 2*2 m**2 and consisting of 200",
                "individual modules. There individual 10 cm thick",
                "detector modules have a sandwichlike structure",
                " (alternating layers of 5 mm iron converter and 5 mm",
                "plastic scintillator). The total thickness of the",
                "detector of 1 m(50% iron, 50% plastic) provides a",
                "detection efficiency of 94% for one single neutron",
                "with kinetic energies around 500 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Since the present experiment detects",
                "coincidences between the Be-10 fragment and one neutron",
                "in the forward direction, only inelastic excitation of",
                "the projectile,i.e. processes electromagnetic",
                "dissociation or Coulomb breakup and nuclear inelastic",
                "scattering into the resonant or nonresonant continuum",
                "contribute to the measured cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
